cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for zero-shot learning using graph convolutional neural networks. This involves designing a new module for knowledge graph propagation, which is a common technique in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
